Looking at the cash flow statement, I see a line item called "Increase (Decrease) in Tax Payable" with a value of 903121.89. This represents the increase in the amount of tax that has been accrued but not yet paid during the period.

The Tax Payable line item is positive, which indicates an increase in the tax liability (taxes accrued but not yet paid).

Therefore, the value of the increase in the amounts of tax accrued but not yet paid is 903121.89.
